ic past. We should rather consider the various permutations of "German" identities that have been negotiated within local and imperial contexts from the early Middle Ages to the present.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturezEurope, German-speakingxHistory and criticism. 0aImperialism in literature. 0aNationalism in literature. 0aNational characteristics, German, in literature. 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)eissuing body,epublisher. 0aSocial history, popular culture, and politics in Germany.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.9771990